messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hey, I need your help.
Okay, tell me where you're at.
Well, the thing is, I was just flying with my buddy.
Flying?
Yeah. We just went down.
Tell me where you were at.
I don't know. We're in the middle of the woods.
You need to tell me what area you were in.
Past 65, heading north. I think down near the river, that's all I know.
He was the experienced flight.
Okay, listen, what's your name?
My name's Tom.
Tom what? He's hurt badly.
I'm William.
Is the aircraft on fire?
No, but it's leaking gas and he's stuck, and I cannot get him out.
So you're up near Goldsbury Road?
I’m not sure, ma'am. I'm not sure. I'm sorry.
That's okay. Are you anywhere near a mailbox or anything?
We're in the middle of a freaking cornfield.
Medic standby for a medical run. Probably battleground.
Tom, do you see a mailbox or a house anywhere around?
No, I don't. I just see a big dirt clot and...
Okay, see if you can see a road anywhere.
Should I leave him? He's hurt badly.
Try to give me a location, Tom. Can you hear me?
Tom, is he breathing?
No, I'm trying to see something.
Okay, that's good.
Yeah, he's bleeding, but I had to leave him.
I understand. You're doing good. Try to find help as quick as you can.
All right. I'll stay on the phone with you.
Do you see a mailbox or a house?
Okay, give me a minute. I'm looking.
If you see a mailbox or a house, let me know.
Oh my God. We're in the middle. They're in a field somewhere.
Tom, are you back at the plane?
No, I see a farmhouse. Should I go to it?
If you can get to it safely, do it. We need a good address.
I want to get help as quickly as we can. I'll try to get there.
Can you get there within a couple of minutes? How far does it look?
Like a football field away.
Okay, do you think you can make it?
Yeah, but what about him?
Yes, that's fine. If you can get help quicker, do it.
All right, I'm going to put the phone in my pocket.
Okay, go ahead.
Help!
Tom, do you see a mailbox?
No, I'm still going.
Give me a minute, okay?
All units be advised, my caller is running to the nearest farmhouse to get an address.
Tom, you're doing good.
Yeah, hold on.
I see a barn. Is there a mailbox at the end of the road?
No, I'm still getting to it.
Hello! I see a house.
Okay, is it a red barn? Could it be a garage that looks like a barn?
It's a red barn, hold on.
Tom, are you down in the river bottoms or up on the hill?
I'm coming down the hill.
He advising he’s coming down the hill. My complainant hears sirens approaching.
Tom, do you see a mailbox?
No, not yet.
Help! I see help!
Tom, do you see the ambulance?
No, but someone is coming.
Okay, what is your address?
I'm on Goldsbury Road.
Do you see a mailbox nearby?
No, but I’ll ask someone.
Okay, tell me from where you're standing, which direction?
If you go to America's and come up to Goldsbury Road, go west.
I'm at 6711 Goldsbury Road.
Okay, so east of this residence, right?
Yes, they're out in the field.
Okay, I'll disconnect now. Thank you.
Thank you so much. Bye.
